Instructions: Ground the situation at the core of each message — write as if living through it, not a generic love message. Use the name naturally if given. Each message should differ: one short and intense, one longer and explanatory, one mildly humorous (if tone fits), one simple and sincere, one from an unexpected angle. Avoid clichés. Return only the numbered list, nothing else.

